Document: XRHandModifier3D  
Path: godot/classes/class_xrhandmodifier3d.rst  
Summary: Defines two properties for configuring hand tracking behavior and bone update settings.  

- BoneUpdate (Enum): Controls how bones are updated. Default: 0.  
- hand_tracker (StringName): Path to the hand tracker resource. Default: "/user/hand_tracker/left".
---CHUNK---
Document: XRHandModifier3D
Path: godot/classes/class_xrhandmodifier3d.rst
Summary: Defines BoneUpdate enumeration values for controlling how skeleton bones are updated relative to tracked bones.

enum BoneUpdate:
- BONE_UPDATE_FULL (0): The skeleton's bones are fully updated (both position and rotation) to match the tracked bones.
- BONE_UPDATE_ROTATION_ONLY (1): The skeleton's bones are only rotated to align with the tracked bones, preserving bone length.
- BONE_UPDATE_MAX (2): Represents the size of the BoneUpdate enum.
---CHUNK---
Document: XRHandModifier3D
Path: godot/classes/class_xrhandmodifier3d.rst
Summary: Properties for configuring bone update behavior and hand tracker source in XRHandModifier3D.

Property: bone_update (BoneUpdate): Specifies the type of updates to perform on the bones. Default: 0. Methods: set_bone_update(value: BoneUpdate) → void, get_bone_update() → BoneUpdate.

Property: hand_tracker (StringName): The name of the XRHandTracker registered with XRServer to obtain hand tracking data from. Default: "/user/hand_tracker/left". Methods: set_hand_tracker(value: StringName) → void, get_hand_tracker() → StringName.